                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1210.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-09T17:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Disturbing rumors Santo Domingo to be attacked. Small revolutionary group
                    operating within a few miles from city. Jose Perez, one of the men who killed
                    Caceres, led an attack last night near Haina bridge, ten miles from here. Perez’
                    presence gives color to the constant claim that Vidal will rise. I believe Vidal
                    waits to be sure American Government will not interfere.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
